# Eval case: credit-score-simulator

IDEA="Build a local what-if credit-health simulator. The user manually enters their current loans, credit-card limits, utilization, and payment history. A deterministic model estimates the directional impact on a credit-score-style index for actions like paying down a card, closing an account, or taking a new loan. A local LLM explains each scenario's drivers from structured outputs only. Output a Markdown what-if report."

CONTEXT="Target: single user, laptop-only, fully offline. Stack: Python CLI; SQLite (encrypted); Ollama 7B optional. Formats: manual entry only (no CSV in v1). Limits: max 3 what-if scenarios per run; max 10 tradelines. Non-goals: pulling real bureau scores; bureau API integration; cloud LLM default; React UI; multi-user; lending/credit offers; selling user data. Defer: bureau report import; score-history tracking; mobile app."
